WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:00.800 align:middle line:90%


00:00:00.800 --> 00:00:03.430 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:03.430 --> 00:00:07.672 align:middle line:90%


00:00:07.672 --> 00:00:09.380 align:middle line:10%
>> Hi, it's James here
from Food Matters,

00:00:09.380 --> 00:00:11.990 align:middle line:10%
and I'm here today
with Kristina Karlsson,

00:00:11.990 --> 00:00:14.480 align:middle line:10%
founder of one of the
most beautiful, stylish,

00:00:14.480 --> 00:00:16.820 align:middle line:10%
and simplistic stationery
companies in the world,

00:00:16.820 --> 00:00:19.640 align:middle line:10%
named after her childhood
nickname, Kikki.

00:00:19.640 --> 00:00:23.210 align:middle line:84%
It's called kikki.K. It's
grown into a global empire

00:00:23.210 --> 00:00:24.530 align:middle line:90%
and has some incredible wares.

00:00:24.530 --> 00:00:25.988 align:middle line:84%
And today we're
going to be talking

00:00:25.988 --> 00:00:30.110 align:middle line:84%
about her book and her mission
to inspire people to dream big.

00:00:30.110 --> 00:00:31.200 align:middle line:90%
Kristina, how are you?

00:00:31.200 --> 00:00:32.000 align:middle line:90%
>> I'm really well.

00:00:32.000 --> 00:00:32.880 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for having me.

00:00:32.880 --> 00:00:33.680 align:middle line:90%
>> That's exciting.

00:00:33.680 --> 00:00:37.580 align:middle line:90%
So your story started--

00:00:37.580 --> 00:00:39.470 align:middle line:84%
it's easy for people
to look at you and go,

00:00:39.470 --> 00:00:41.840 align:middle line:84%
wow, you're the
successful founder

00:00:41.840 --> 00:00:43.720 align:middle line:84%
of this beautiful
company and so stylish

00:00:43.720 --> 00:00:45.240 align:middle line:84%
and jet setting
around the world.

00:00:45.240 --> 00:00:48.710 align:middle line:84%
But your story started in a
very different fashion, right?

00:00:48.710 --> 00:00:51.973 align:middle line:84%
You moved to Australia and were
a bit lost for what to do next.

00:00:51.973 --> 00:00:53.390 align:middle line:84%
Can you tell me
what was happening

00:00:53.390 --> 00:00:54.470 align:middle line:90%
at that stage of your life?

00:00:54.470 --> 00:00:55.270 align:middle line:90%
>> Absolutely.

00:00:55.270 --> 00:00:58.160 align:middle line:84%
So I grew up in Sweden, and
then I worked in a ski resort

00:00:58.160 --> 00:01:00.920 align:middle line:84%
in Austria, where I
met my partner, Paul.

00:01:00.920 --> 00:01:03.530 align:middle line:84%
And he was from
Australia, so I decided

00:01:03.530 --> 00:01:06.450 align:middle line:90%
to go with him to Australia.

00:01:06.450 --> 00:01:09.230 align:middle line:84%
And when I decided to stay
in Australia, I thought,

00:01:09.230 --> 00:01:11.570 align:middle line:84%
if I'm going to stay here,
I have to do something

00:01:11.570 --> 00:01:13.130 align:middle line:90%
that I really love.

00:01:13.130 --> 00:01:15.190 align:middle line:84%
And that was not
so easy to find,

00:01:15.190 --> 00:01:17.210 align:middle line:84%
and I was whingeing
and complaining,

00:01:17.210 --> 00:01:19.250 align:middle line:84%
and I just was a
little bit unsettled.

00:01:19.250 --> 00:01:23.300 align:middle line:84%
And I think I was asking
Paul like five times a day,

00:01:23.300 --> 00:01:24.770 align:middle line:84%
what am I going to
do with my life?

00:01:24.770 --> 00:01:26.960 align:middle line:84%
And one morning at
3:00 AM, I woke him up,

00:01:26.960 --> 00:01:28.880 align:middle line:84%
I think for the fifth
time, saying, what am I

00:01:28.880 --> 00:01:29.960 align:middle line:90%
going to do with my life?

00:01:29.960 --> 00:01:34.730 align:middle line:84%
And he then very nicely
turned on the light

00:01:34.730 --> 00:01:38.100 align:middle line:84%
and said, why don't we write
down what's important to you?

00:01:38.100 --> 00:01:38.900 align:middle line:90%
And at 3:00 AM--

00:01:38.900 --> 00:01:40.040 align:middle line:90%
I call it my 3:00 AM list--

00:01:40.040 --> 00:01:43.640 align:middle line:84%
I wrote down that I wanted to
drive to work every single day

00:01:43.640 --> 00:01:45.620 align:middle line:84%
and really loving
what I was doing.

00:01:45.620 --> 00:01:47.270 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to have a
business on my own,

00:01:47.270 --> 00:01:49.590 align:middle line:84%
but I had no idea what
that was going to be.

00:01:49.590 --> 00:01:51.380 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to have a
connection with Sweden.

00:01:51.380 --> 00:01:52.970 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to work
with Swedish design

00:01:52.970 --> 00:01:54.470 align:middle line:84%
because that was
one of my passions.

00:01:54.470 --> 00:01:57.530 align:middle line:84%
And then I wanted
to make $500 a week.

00:01:57.530 --> 00:02:00.590 align:middle line:84%
And that kind of was my
first dreams on paper.

00:02:00.590 --> 00:02:02.780 align:middle line:84%
And then when I looked
at that-- and it's

00:02:02.780 --> 00:02:04.550 align:middle line:84%
a bit of a longer
story than this,

00:02:04.550 --> 00:02:08.639 align:middle line:84%
but to make it a long story
short, I looked at that paper,

00:02:08.639 --> 00:02:11.480 align:middle line:84%
and I thought, if I'm going to
have my own business one day,

00:02:11.480 --> 00:02:13.310 align:middle line:84%
I have to have
beautiful stationery.

00:02:13.310 --> 00:02:16.010 align:middle line:84%
And I was growing up in
Sweden with beautiful design

00:02:16.010 --> 00:02:19.500 align:middle line:84%
around me, and I wanted to have
something that was inspiring,

00:02:19.500 --> 00:02:22.370 align:middle line:84%
but also beautifully
designed and good quality.

00:02:22.370 --> 00:02:24.357 align:middle line:90%
And I wanted to be organized.

00:02:24.357 --> 00:02:26.690 align:middle line:84%
So I thought, I'm going to
go out and buy some products.

00:02:26.690 --> 00:02:28.820 align:middle line:84%
And I just could
not find anything.

00:02:28.820 --> 00:02:30.862 align:middle line:90%
And then I got--

00:02:30.862 --> 00:02:31.820 align:middle line:90%
I didn't get depressed.

00:02:31.820 --> 00:02:32.610 align:middle line:90%
That's not the right word.

00:02:32.610 --> 00:02:33.947 align:middle line:90%
But I was like, this is boring.

00:02:33.947 --> 00:02:35.780 align:middle line:84%
And then I got super
excited, and I thought,

00:02:35.780 --> 00:02:37.790 align:middle line:84%
I'm actually going to
start my own business,

00:02:37.790 --> 00:02:39.860 align:middle line:84%
and I'm going to open
beautiful Swedish design

00:02:39.860 --> 00:02:42.980 align:middle line:84%
stores specializing
in stationery

00:02:42.980 --> 00:02:45.110 align:middle line:84%
in my favorite cities,
being Paris, London, New

00:02:45.110 --> 00:02:48.890 align:middle line:84%
York, et cetera, Sydney,
Copenhagen, London, whatever.

00:02:48.890 --> 00:02:51.860 align:middle line:90%
And I just started.

00:02:51.860 --> 00:02:54.200 align:middle line:90%
And kikki.K. was born.

00:02:54.200 --> 00:02:57.440 align:middle line:84%
>> So the name was after
a nickname that you had

00:02:57.440 --> 00:02:59.060 align:middle line:90%
at school, right?

00:02:59.060 --> 00:03:00.990 align:middle line:90%
How did that come about?

00:03:00.990 --> 00:03:04.100 align:middle line:84%
>> I was having dinner with
a friend who was a graphic

00:03:04.100 --> 00:03:08.750 align:middle line:84%
designer, and I liked
K as the letter.

00:03:08.750 --> 00:03:11.975 align:middle line:84%
And because I spelled
Kikki with K-I-KK-I,

00:03:11.975 --> 00:03:14.480 align:middle line:84%
it looked really
beautiful graphically.

00:03:14.480 --> 00:03:16.520 align:middle line:90%
And my last name was Karlsson.

00:03:16.520 --> 00:03:19.550 align:middle line:84%
So I put it on a
little serviette,

00:03:19.550 --> 00:03:20.872 align:middle line:90%
and we were having dinner.

00:03:20.872 --> 00:03:22.580 align:middle line:84%
It was like a Tuesday
night or something.

00:03:22.580 --> 00:03:25.102 align:middle line:84%
And he had young kids,
and he was saying,

00:03:25.102 --> 00:03:26.310 align:middle line:90%
let's put it on the computer.

00:03:26.310 --> 00:03:28.910 align:middle line:90%
And I said, no, not now.

00:03:28.910 --> 00:03:31.310 align:middle line:84%
And we did it, and it's
never been changed since.

00:03:31.310 --> 00:03:34.040 align:middle line:84%
Well, it has been changed
a couple of times lately,

00:03:34.040 --> 00:03:36.620 align:middle line:84%
but for a long time,
it was the same.

00:03:36.620 --> 00:03:40.550 align:middle line:84%
>> And how old were you when you
sort of came up with this idea

00:03:40.550 --> 00:03:44.990 align:middle line:84%
for kikki.K, and what
has it grown into today?

00:03:44.990 --> 00:03:47.300 align:middle line:84%
>> So I was 22 when
I came to Australia,

00:03:47.300 --> 00:03:51.980 align:middle line:84%
so it took me a couple of years
before I came up with the idea.

00:03:51.980 --> 00:03:55.580 align:middle line:84%
And it started
with me asking Paul

00:03:55.580 --> 00:03:59.210 align:middle line:84%
if he would sell his house
to open our first store.

00:03:59.210 --> 00:04:02.060 align:middle line:84%
I had this dream to
open around the world,

00:04:02.060 --> 00:04:03.842 align:middle line:84%
and I just didn't
have any money.

00:04:03.842 --> 00:04:05.300 align:middle line:84%
So I thought, we
have to get going.

00:04:05.300 --> 00:04:08.480 align:middle line:84%
So Paul sold his house
to open the first store.

00:04:08.480 --> 00:04:12.620 align:middle line:84%
And now we have over 100
stores in five countries,

00:04:12.620 --> 00:04:15.653 align:middle line:84%
and we sell to 147 countries
online, which blows

00:04:15.653 --> 00:04:16.820 align:middle line:90%
my mind every time I say it.

00:04:16.820 --> 00:04:20.750 align:middle line:84%
So it's an exciting journey,
and my biggest dream now

00:04:20.750 --> 00:04:24.830 align:middle line:84%
is to inspire 101 million people
to write down three dreams

00:04:24.830 --> 00:04:26.993 align:middle line:90%
and then go and chase them.

00:04:26.993 --> 00:04:28.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Was there a part
of you that thought,

00:04:28.660 --> 00:04:30.400 align:middle line:84%
there's no way this
is going to happen?

00:04:30.400 --> 00:04:31.990 align:middle line:84%
Or did you just
believe it so much

00:04:31.990 --> 00:04:34.140 align:middle line:84%
that you just pushed
through all obstacles?

00:04:34.140 --> 00:04:36.370 align:middle line:84%
>> I think we all
deal with self-doubt.

00:04:36.370 --> 00:04:39.010 align:middle line:84%
So having those
big dreams on paper

00:04:39.010 --> 00:04:41.050 align:middle line:90%
seemed impossible at the time.

00:04:41.050 --> 00:04:43.800 align:middle line:84%
But because they were dreams,
I felt like, let's just

00:04:43.800 --> 00:04:45.040 align:middle line:90%
start somewhere.

00:04:45.040 --> 00:04:46.690 align:middle line:90%
And there's a quote that I love.

00:04:46.690 --> 00:04:48.190 align:middle line:84%
You don't have to
be great to start,

00:04:48.190 --> 00:04:50.680 align:middle line:84%
but you actually have
to start to be great.

00:04:50.680 --> 00:04:52.540 align:middle line:90%
And I just started.

00:04:52.540 --> 00:04:56.020 align:middle line:84%
And because I was so excited
about this big vision

00:04:56.020 --> 00:04:59.930 align:middle line:84%
and this big dream,
I just kept going,

00:04:59.930 --> 00:05:01.120 align:middle line:90%
and I was just so excited.

00:05:01.120 --> 00:05:03.700 align:middle line:84%
And I was talking to
suppliers about opening stores

00:05:03.700 --> 00:05:05.230 align:middle line:84%
around the world,
but I had no idea

00:05:05.230 --> 00:05:06.522 align:middle line:90%
how to put together a notebook.

00:05:06.522 --> 00:05:09.850 align:middle line:84%
So of course some people
thought I was absolutely mad.

00:05:09.850 --> 00:05:12.202 align:middle line:84%
But there's another
really good quote,

00:05:12.202 --> 00:05:13.660 align:middle line:84%
which is, it's
really good that you

00:05:13.660 --> 00:05:14.952 align:middle line:90%
don't know what you don't know.

00:05:14.952 --> 00:05:17.320 align:middle line:84%
Because if you knew what
you have to go through,

00:05:17.320 --> 00:05:20.160 align:middle line:84%
all the challenges that
we all have to go through,

00:05:20.160 --> 00:05:22.360 align:middle line:84%
it's good sometimes
not knowing that.

00:05:22.360 --> 00:05:25.480 align:middle line:84%
And I think there's
four things that really

00:05:25.480 --> 00:05:27.260 align:middle line:90%
got to where we are today.

00:05:27.260 --> 00:05:28.450 align:middle line:90%
Number one is passion.

00:05:28.450 --> 00:05:31.900 align:middle line:84%
I really, truly believe that
if you do something you love,

00:05:31.900 --> 00:05:34.510 align:middle line:84%
you are going to get
through all the challenges.

00:05:34.510 --> 00:05:36.700 align:middle line:84%
Because regardless
how good our plan is,

00:05:36.700 --> 00:05:38.020 align:middle line:90%
there is always challenges.

00:05:38.020 --> 00:05:40.670 align:middle line:84%
In a small business
or in life in general,

00:05:40.670 --> 00:05:43.400 align:middle line:84%
there's not smooth sailing
all the way through life.

00:05:43.400 --> 00:05:47.420 align:middle line:84%
So doing something you
love is so, so important.

00:05:47.420 --> 00:05:49.960 align:middle line:90%
Number two is vision.

00:05:49.960 --> 00:05:51.640 align:middle line:84%
I think having a
clear vision, like I

00:05:51.640 --> 00:05:55.220 align:middle line:84%
had all these amazing
locations mapped out,

00:05:55.220 --> 00:05:57.040 align:middle line:84%
and I put clocks up
in the office walls

00:05:57.040 --> 00:06:02.080 align:middle line:84%
to really make sure that we
were working towards that.

00:06:02.080 --> 00:06:04.600 align:middle line:84%
So having a clear vision
was also really important

00:06:04.600 --> 00:06:08.050 align:middle line:84%
in terms of when
tough times hit us,

00:06:08.050 --> 00:06:11.410 align:middle line:84%
which they have throughout the
years, and also for the team

00:06:11.410 --> 00:06:14.432 align:middle line:84%
to know where we're going,
so having that clear vision.

00:06:14.432 --> 00:06:15.640 align:middle line:90%
Number three is don't say no.

00:06:15.640 --> 00:06:16.480 align:middle line:90%
Say how.

00:06:16.480 --> 00:06:19.330 align:middle line:84%
I think as a small business,
most small businesses,

00:06:19.330 --> 00:06:22.180 align:middle line:84%
with the statistics, it's
they fail really quickly.

00:06:22.180 --> 00:06:25.540 align:middle line:84%
And not giving up, I
think, is a key ingredient

00:06:25.540 --> 00:06:27.560 align:middle line:84%
to really succeed
when you start.

00:06:27.560 --> 00:06:30.110 align:middle line:84%
So in our office wall,
we have don't say no.

00:06:30.110 --> 00:06:30.910 align:middle line:90%
Say how.

00:06:30.910 --> 00:06:32.130 align:middle line:90%
There is always a way.

00:06:32.130 --> 00:06:34.870 align:middle line:84%
But sometimes you have
to look at your ways

00:06:34.870 --> 00:06:36.230 align:middle line:90%
in a different way.

00:06:36.230 --> 00:06:38.080 align:middle line:84%
And then the fourth
one is dreaming.

00:06:38.080 --> 00:06:41.398 align:middle line:84%
Because I dream in
my personal life,

00:06:41.398 --> 00:06:42.940 align:middle line:84%
but I also dream
within the business.

00:06:42.940 --> 00:06:46.060 align:middle line:84%
Because then it takes all
the restrictions away.

00:06:46.060 --> 00:06:48.280 align:middle line:84%
Because if you just look
at what's realistic,

00:06:48.280 --> 00:06:52.030 align:middle line:84%
you probably wouldn't be able
to do what you want to do.

00:06:52.030 --> 00:06:57.200 align:middle line:84%
So dreaming is a really big part
of starting a business as well.

00:06:57.200 --> 00:07:02.680 align:middle line:84%
>> So part of that dream to
help bring your idea of dreaming

00:07:02.680 --> 00:07:04.850 align:middle line:84%
to other people was to
write a book, right?

00:07:04.850 --> 00:07:05.650 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep.

00:07:05.650 --> 00:07:09.190 align:middle line:84%
>> And in that book, you sort
of break down this process

00:07:09.190 --> 00:07:10.420 align:middle line:90%
of setting goals.

00:07:10.420 --> 00:07:11.220 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep.

00:07:11.220 --> 00:07:14.290 align:middle line:84%
>> And one of the things that
people first confront when they

00:07:14.290 --> 00:07:16.300 align:middle line:84%
set goals is they start
writing them down,

00:07:16.300 --> 00:07:18.430 align:middle line:84%
but then they start
thinking to themselves,

00:07:18.430 --> 00:07:20.680 align:middle line:84%
there's no way I'm going to
be able to do that, right?

00:07:20.680 --> 00:07:24.170 align:middle line:84%
This self-limiting
voice comes in.

00:07:24.170 --> 00:07:26.290 align:middle line:84%
Tell me about what's
happening in that process

00:07:26.290 --> 00:07:28.100 align:middle line:84%
and how people can
move through it.

00:07:28.100 --> 00:07:32.660 align:middle line:84%
>> Yeah, well, I think if we
are starting by setting goals,

00:07:32.660 --> 00:07:34.030 align:middle line:90%
we often stretch ourselves.

00:07:34.030 --> 00:07:35.560 align:middle line:84%
We might look at
where we are today,

00:07:35.560 --> 00:07:38.590 align:middle line:84%
and we might say, well,
my next step in my career.

00:07:38.590 --> 00:07:40.420 align:middle line:84%
Or it might be
that I want to run

00:07:40.420 --> 00:07:43.090 align:middle line:84%
a bit further or a
bit faster or whatever

00:07:43.090 --> 00:07:44.830 align:middle line:84%
it is in terms of
different goals

00:07:44.830 --> 00:07:47.050 align:middle line:84%
and different
aspects of your life.

00:07:47.050 --> 00:07:49.150 align:middle line:84%
But I think if you do
that, you limit yourself.

00:07:49.150 --> 00:07:52.210 align:middle line:84%
Because then you
might have been all

00:07:52.210 --> 00:07:54.640 align:middle line:84%
of a sudden in a role that
might not be your dream role,

00:07:54.640 --> 00:07:59.090 align:middle line:84%
and it might be not your
dream life as it is right now.

00:07:59.090 --> 00:08:01.030 align:middle line:84%
So I like to not
think about goals.

00:08:01.030 --> 00:08:03.220 align:middle line:90%
I like to start with dreaming.

00:08:03.220 --> 00:08:05.800 align:middle line:84%
And then I like to ask
myself a few questions.

00:08:05.800 --> 00:08:08.470 align:middle line:84%
And that is, what would you
do if you couldn't fail?

00:08:08.470 --> 00:08:12.160 align:middle line:84%
If you had all the money,
because often money restricts

00:08:12.160 --> 00:08:14.760 align:middle line:84%
the way that we think that we
can do things because we say,

00:08:14.760 --> 00:08:16.510 align:middle line:84%
I can't do that because
I can't afford it,

00:08:16.510 --> 00:08:20.100 align:middle line:84%
or it's not possible because
of my salary or whatever.

00:08:20.100 --> 00:08:21.850 align:middle line:84%
So what would you do
if you couldn't fail?

00:08:21.850 --> 00:08:25.000 align:middle line:84%
If you had all the money, the
resources, and the knowledge,

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:27.370 align:middle line:84%
and the time, and
the energy and health

00:08:27.370 --> 00:08:30.220 align:middle line:84%
to do whatever you
want to do in life?

00:08:30.220 --> 00:08:33.010 align:middle line:84%
Then it often brings
up things that

00:08:33.010 --> 00:08:38.120 align:middle line:84%
might be completely different
to where we are right now today.

00:08:38.120 --> 00:08:43.419 align:middle line:84%
So I think we are very
encouraged by parents, perhaps.

00:08:43.419 --> 00:08:46.283 align:middle line:84%
Schools-- you might be super
smart in school and end up

00:08:46.283 --> 00:08:48.700 align:middle line:84%
in the most amazing school,
and then you go to university,

00:08:48.700 --> 00:08:52.690 align:middle line:84%
and all of a sudden you are
in a role that maybe was

00:08:52.690 --> 00:08:55.610 align:middle line:84%
your parents' dreams or your
teachers' because you were

00:08:55.610 --> 00:08:56.410 align:middle line:90%
so talented.

00:08:56.410 --> 00:09:00.760 align:middle line:84%
So I meet a lot of people when
I do my talks and my workshops

00:09:00.760 --> 00:09:05.180 align:middle line:84%
about dreaming that actually
are not living their own dream

00:09:05.180 --> 00:09:05.980 align:middle line:90%
life.

00:09:05.980 --> 00:09:09.940 align:middle line:84%
They are either influenced
by parents or schools

00:09:09.940 --> 00:09:13.620 align:middle line:84%
or social media today
as well, of course.

00:09:13.620 --> 00:09:16.980 align:middle line:84%
>> Talking to that
point a little bit,

00:09:16.980 --> 00:09:20.640 align:middle line:84%
how do you feel the culture sort
of impacts the dreams that we

00:09:20.640 --> 00:09:24.810 align:middle line:84%
set, and/or schooling
or social media?

00:09:24.810 --> 00:09:26.850 align:middle line:84%
Because a lot of the
times we're setting goals

00:09:26.850 --> 00:09:28.590 align:middle line:90%
that are very materialistic.

00:09:28.590 --> 00:09:34.710 align:middle line:84%
It's like things, accumulating
houses, cars, planes,

00:09:34.710 --> 00:09:36.030 align:middle line:90%
whatever it is.

00:09:36.030 --> 00:09:37.680 align:middle line:90%
And yet we're not--

00:09:37.680 --> 00:09:39.600 align:middle line:84%
I feel like we're getting
that from society.

00:09:39.600 --> 00:09:40.892 align:middle line:90%
We're getting that from social.

00:09:40.892 --> 00:09:45.000 align:middle line:84%
What do you think is influencing
this nature of goal setting?

00:09:45.000 --> 00:09:46.830 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think
in today's world,

00:09:46.830 --> 00:09:50.242 align:middle line:84%
you can see what everyone
else, what they're doing,

00:09:50.242 --> 00:09:51.450 align:middle line:90%
but also what they're having.

00:09:51.450 --> 00:09:53.730 align:middle line:84%
And if people are
doing well, they

00:09:53.730 --> 00:09:55.680 align:middle line:90%
might be posting about that.

00:09:55.680 --> 00:09:59.160 align:middle line:84%
They might not post about how
they worked so hard to get it.

00:09:59.160 --> 00:10:01.110 align:middle line:84%
So I think we're
influenced by that.

00:10:01.110 --> 00:10:03.720 align:middle line:84%
And of course, we all want
to live in the most beautiful

00:10:03.720 --> 00:10:06.230 align:middle line:84%
home, and we all want to
drive the car of our dreams

00:10:06.230 --> 00:10:07.380 align:middle line:90%
or whatever.

00:10:07.380 --> 00:10:10.300 align:middle line:84%
So I think that's just a
natural thing that we do,

00:10:10.300 --> 00:10:12.690 align:middle line:84%
because that's what
a lot of people do.

00:10:12.690 --> 00:10:17.350 align:middle line:84%
But the way that I do it is
to dream in different areas.

00:10:17.350 --> 00:10:19.338 align:middle line:84%
So what are your
dreams for your health?

00:10:19.338 --> 00:10:21.130 align:middle line:84%
If you could have
anything for your health,

00:10:21.130 --> 00:10:22.070 align:middle line:90%
what would that be?

00:10:22.070 --> 00:10:23.820 align:middle line:84%
Would you be the fittest
you've ever been,

00:10:23.820 --> 00:10:27.970 align:middle line:84%
or would you start yoga or
meditation or whatever it is?

00:10:27.970 --> 00:10:30.960 align:middle line:84%
And then I also think that we
should dream for our community.

00:10:30.960 --> 00:10:35.310 align:middle line:84%
So we might be heartbroken
because you lost someone,

00:10:35.310 --> 00:10:38.412 align:middle line:84%
or someone was ill, or you
might have an illness yourself.

00:10:38.412 --> 00:10:39.870 align:middle line:84%
So you might feel
really passionate

00:10:39.870 --> 00:10:43.650 align:middle line:84%
about something that
has influenced you.

00:10:43.650 --> 00:10:46.680 align:middle line:84%
So I think dreaming in
the community areas,

00:10:46.680 --> 00:10:49.050 align:middle line:84%
dreaming about health,
but then also dreaming

00:10:49.050 --> 00:10:51.480 align:middle line:84%
about your career and
your life and your family

00:10:51.480 --> 00:10:54.000 align:middle line:90%
or relationships or friends.

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:56.700 align:middle line:84%
So I think you should
dream in all aspects,

00:10:56.700 --> 00:10:59.290 align:middle line:84%
not just about what you
actually want to buy.

00:10:59.290 --> 00:11:02.690 align:middle line:84%
And most of my dreams
now are fun dreams

00:11:02.690 --> 00:11:04.350 align:middle line:84%
of things that I
want to travel to

00:11:04.350 --> 00:11:07.050 align:middle line:84%
and things I want
to do with my family

00:11:07.050 --> 00:11:11.100 align:middle line:84%
or friends or people I
want to meet, for example.

00:11:11.100 --> 00:11:15.100 align:middle line:84%
In my book, I have a
whole 101 people to meet,

00:11:15.100 --> 00:11:18.030 align:middle line:84%
because I just find the most
interesting thing in life

00:11:18.030 --> 00:11:20.340 align:middle line:90%
is to meet interesting people.

00:11:20.340 --> 00:11:23.010 align:middle line:84%
So I just add to that all the
time when I read about someone

00:11:23.010 --> 00:11:27.180 align:middle line:84%
or see someone interesting
on television or in a book

00:11:27.180 --> 00:11:28.020 align:middle line:90%
or whatever.

00:11:28.020 --> 00:11:32.940 align:middle line:84%
So I love dreaming because
there is no limits to dreaming.

00:11:32.940 --> 00:11:34.583 align:middle line:90%
>> And let's speak to that.

00:11:34.583 --> 00:11:36.500 align:middle line:84%
I want to speak to
something else in a second.

00:11:36.500 --> 00:11:38.920 align:middle line:84%
But can you tell me about
some of your dreams?

00:11:38.920 --> 00:11:40.590 align:middle line:84%
Because I love how
obscure they are,

00:11:40.590 --> 00:11:43.453 align:middle line:84%
like riding Icelandic horses
or going or African safari,

00:11:43.453 --> 00:11:45.120 align:middle line:84%
which you did with
your family recently.

00:11:45.120 --> 00:11:47.090 align:middle line:84%
So tell me about some
of the experience dreams

00:11:47.090 --> 00:11:48.060 align:middle line:90%
that you wrote down.

00:11:48.060 --> 00:11:48.860 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:11:48.860 --> 00:11:50.960 align:middle line:84%
So one of my dreams,
which I think

00:11:50.960 --> 00:11:53.170 align:middle line:84%
is very suitable
for this program,

00:11:53.170 --> 00:11:56.123 align:middle line:84%
is I want to be a
yoga teacher one day.

00:11:56.123 --> 00:11:58.040 align:middle line:84%
But I don't have time
for that now because you

00:11:58.040 --> 00:12:00.380 align:middle line:84%
have to do a lot of
hours, and I want

00:12:00.380 --> 00:12:04.040 align:middle line:84%
to just do yoga when I feel
like it, not because I have to.

00:12:04.040 --> 00:12:08.180 align:middle line:84%
So I decided that I wanted
to become a yoga teacher when

00:12:08.180 --> 00:12:13.220 align:middle line:84%
I'm 60 because my dream
is to live till I'm 120.

00:12:13.220 --> 00:12:16.300 align:middle line:84%
So I'm thinking if I start at
60, I have quite a few years

00:12:16.300 --> 00:12:17.450 align:middle line:90%
to practice yoga.

00:12:17.450 --> 00:12:19.520 align:middle line:84%
And it's funny because
I actually then started

00:12:19.520 --> 00:12:25.430 align:middle line:84%
to search for yoga teachers,
and I found one yoga teacher who

00:12:25.430 --> 00:12:29.120 align:middle line:84%
is still practicing yoga and
teaching yoga in New York,

00:12:29.120 --> 00:12:31.550 align:middle line:90%
and she is 101.

00:12:31.550 --> 00:12:34.470 align:middle line:84%
So things like
that is really fun.

00:12:34.470 --> 00:12:38.690 align:middle line:84%
Other dreams that I have are
to give a brilliant speech

00:12:38.690 --> 00:12:41.730 align:middle line:90%
when my son is turning 50.

00:12:41.730 --> 00:12:44.270 align:middle line:84%
So that means that I have to
be really healthy because I

00:12:44.270 --> 00:12:45.890 align:middle line:90%
will be a bit older then.

00:12:45.890 --> 00:12:49.460 align:middle line:84%
And I want to say something
really funny and good,

00:12:49.460 --> 00:12:53.090 align:middle line:84%
so it's another incentive
to really keep healthy.

00:12:53.090 --> 00:12:56.960 align:middle line:84%
But then I also want to
build my own dream home.

00:12:56.960 --> 00:13:01.070 align:middle line:84%
I want to live like two months
in all my favorite cities

00:13:01.070 --> 00:13:05.400 align:middle line:84%
as a local, not just in a hotel
and do all the typical tourist

00:13:05.400 --> 00:13:06.200 align:middle line:90%
stuff.

00:13:06.200 --> 00:13:09.440 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to experience different
cultures and meet local people

00:13:09.440 --> 00:13:10.967 align:middle line:90%
and live in a home.

00:13:10.967 --> 00:13:12.050 align:middle line:90%
So there's lots of dreams.

00:13:12.050 --> 00:13:15.170 align:middle line:84%
And every day I
add to my dreams.

00:13:15.170 --> 00:13:16.710 align:middle line:84%
I think it's so
much fun to dream.

00:13:16.710 --> 00:13:17.510 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:13:17.510 --> 00:13:18.770 align:middle line:90%
Beautiful.

00:13:18.770 --> 00:13:20.900 align:middle line:84%
In your book, there's
the lady from Zimbabwe

00:13:20.900 --> 00:13:23.890 align:middle line:84%
who's become one of
Oprah's favorite people.

00:13:23.890 --> 00:13:27.410 align:middle line:84%
And I found her story so
inspirational, so incredible,

00:13:27.410 --> 00:13:32.090 align:middle line:84%
just how even dreaming
big with having access

00:13:32.090 --> 00:13:37.160 align:middle line:84%
to no resources, no wealth,
really in a very dire state

00:13:37.160 --> 00:13:40.220 align:middle line:84%
can still open up-- there's
possibilities that can open up

00:13:40.220 --> 00:13:41.390 align:middle line:90%
and that things can happen.

00:13:41.390 --> 00:13:44.840 align:middle line:84%
Because I think that she's maybe
created this environment of,

00:13:44.840 --> 00:13:45.850 align:middle line:90%
this is a possibility.

00:13:45.850 --> 00:13:46.850 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:13:46.850 --> 00:13:50.300 align:middle line:84%
>> But there was a grandmother
or an advisor or somebody

00:13:50.300 --> 00:13:52.050 align:middle line:84%
in her community
that said, wait,

00:13:52.050 --> 00:13:54.665 align:middle line:84%
you have to add one more
dream to your dreams.

00:13:54.665 --> 00:13:55.790 align:middle line:90%
It can't just be about you.

00:13:55.790 --> 00:13:57.207 align:middle line:84%
It has to be about
your community.

00:13:57.207 --> 00:13:58.782 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep.

00:13:58.782 --> 00:14:00.740 align:middle line:84%
>> Maybe tell me a little
bit about that story.

00:14:00.740 --> 00:14:02.360 align:middle line:84%
Because you went and met
with her recently, right?

00:14:02.360 --> 00:14:02.570 align:middle line:90%
>> Yes.

00:14:02.570 --> 00:14:03.370 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:14:03.370 --> 00:14:05.930 align:middle line:84%
Maybe tell me a little
bit about that story,

00:14:05.930 --> 00:14:08.210 align:middle line:84%
how you had one of
your goals to meet her,

00:14:08.210 --> 00:14:09.710 align:middle line:90%
and how you did meet her.

00:14:09.710 --> 00:14:11.570 align:middle line:84%
And then the aspect
of her making

00:14:11.570 --> 00:14:14.340 align:middle line:84%
it bigger than just her
dream of going to university.

00:14:14.340 --> 00:14:15.590 align:middle line:90%
It became about the community.

00:14:15.590 --> 00:14:17.132 align:middle line:84%
I'd love to hear
that story from you.

00:14:17.132 --> 00:14:18.290 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, absolutely.

00:14:18.290 --> 00:14:22.940 align:middle line:84%
So when I wrote my book, I kept
thinking about the young people

00:14:22.940 --> 00:14:26.980 align:middle line:84%
in my life that could
benefit from the dreaming

00:14:26.980 --> 00:14:27.780 align:middle line:90%
that I've done.

00:14:27.780 --> 00:14:30.740 align:middle line:84%
And I wanted to pass
on what I've learned.

00:14:30.740 --> 00:14:33.980 align:middle line:84%
But then I kept thinking
about my book group, who

00:14:33.980 --> 00:14:37.710 align:middle line:84%
are in my age or older, and
they all achieved so many

00:14:37.710 --> 00:14:38.510 align:middle line:90%
of their dreams.

00:14:38.510 --> 00:14:40.400 align:middle line:84%
And I was thinking,
I wonder if they

00:14:40.400 --> 00:14:43.820 align:middle line:84%
would love dreaming as
much as these young people

00:14:43.820 --> 00:14:45.170 align:middle line:90%
that I'm trying to encourage.

00:14:45.170 --> 00:14:49.340 align:middle line:84%
So I did this exercise, which is
in my book, called 101 dreams.

00:14:49.340 --> 00:14:53.270 align:middle line:84%
And I realized, of course, it
has nothing to do with age.

00:14:53.270 --> 00:14:54.920 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't matter
how old you are

00:14:54.920 --> 00:14:59.330 align:middle line:84%
because you will keep dreaming
until your end of your life.

00:14:59.330 --> 00:15:01.940 align:middle line:84%
And one of my
girlfriends, Anna Coren,

00:15:01.940 --> 00:15:03.950 align:middle line:90%
she called me the day after.

00:15:03.950 --> 00:15:05.450 align:middle line:90%
She was so inspired by dreaming.

00:15:05.450 --> 00:15:08.870 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I came across
this amazing woman who

00:15:08.870 --> 00:15:12.120 align:middle line:84%
is an African lady, but she
is like a dreamer like you.

00:15:12.120 --> 00:15:14.120 align:middle line:84%
So she said, you have to
listen to this podcast.

00:15:14.120 --> 00:15:18.330 align:middle line:84%
So I did, and that is when
everything came together

00:15:18.330 --> 00:15:19.130 align:middle line:90%
for me.

00:15:19.130 --> 00:15:20.820 align:middle line:84%
Because when I was
writing the book,

00:15:20.820 --> 00:15:24.080 align:middle line:84%
I wanted to do something
for someone else.

00:15:24.080 --> 00:15:25.490 align:middle line:90%
I wanted to support a charity.

00:15:25.490 --> 00:15:27.320 align:middle line:84%
And we support a lot
of things at kikki.K,

00:15:27.320 --> 00:15:29.900 align:middle line:84%
but we haven't
found one that felt

00:15:29.900 --> 00:15:32.090 align:middle line:90%
like really aligned with us.

00:15:32.090 --> 00:15:35.880 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, this is
perfect because Tererai,

00:15:35.880 --> 00:15:38.210 align:middle line:84%
she has like 12 schools
in Zimbabwe now.

00:15:38.210 --> 00:15:39.200 align:middle line:90%
So we have stationery.

00:15:39.200 --> 00:15:41.750 align:middle line:84%
So we've just given
stationery to all the schools.

00:15:41.750 --> 00:15:44.850 align:middle line:84%
And she is also a dreamer,
and it really connects us.

00:15:44.850 --> 00:15:47.570 align:middle line:84%
So I contacted her
and I said, I would

00:15:47.570 --> 00:15:49.850 align:middle line:90%
love to support your schools.

00:15:49.850 --> 00:15:55.460 align:middle line:84%
And my dream is to give a
US dollar per book sold.

00:15:55.460 --> 00:15:58.255 align:middle line:84%
And my dream is to sell 1
million books so I can give her

00:15:58.255 --> 00:15:59.570 align:middle line:90%
a million dollars.

00:15:59.570 --> 00:16:01.490 align:middle line:84%
And I think she thought
I was a bit crazy

00:16:01.490 --> 00:16:05.270 align:middle line:84%
because, of course, first
sell 1 million books is not

00:16:05.270 --> 00:16:06.290 align:middle line:90%
the easiest task.

00:16:06.290 --> 00:16:07.130 align:middle line:90%
[LAUGHS]

00:16:07.130 --> 00:16:10.850 align:middle line:84%
But that's what I'm
working all the time

00:16:10.850 --> 00:16:13.392 align:middle line:84%
to see if I can
achieve that, but also

00:16:13.392 --> 00:16:15.350 align:middle line:84%
being able to support
the stationery and things

00:16:15.350 --> 00:16:16.150 align:middle line:90%
like that.

00:16:16.150 --> 00:16:19.190 align:middle line:84%
So I contacted her, and
when I launched a book,

00:16:19.190 --> 00:16:21.380 align:middle line:84%
we did the book
signings together.

00:16:21.380 --> 00:16:24.390 align:middle line:90%
And she is an amazing woman.

00:16:24.390 --> 00:16:26.360 align:middle line:90%
She is my biggest inspiration.

00:16:26.360 --> 00:16:29.450 align:middle line:84%
And the reason why I share
her story both in my book,

00:16:29.450 --> 00:16:31.280 align:middle line:84%
but also on my
podcast, is because she

00:16:31.280 --> 00:16:33.210 align:middle line:90%
had absolutely nothing.

00:16:33.210 --> 00:16:36.410 align:middle line:84%
So Tererai, she grew up
in a culture in Zimbabwe

00:16:36.410 --> 00:16:40.040 align:middle line:84%
where she was married away
as an 11-year-old girl.

00:16:40.040 --> 00:16:42.650 align:middle line:84%
And she had I think
five kids before 18

00:16:42.650 --> 00:16:49.730 align:middle line:84%
and abused and lived in a very
challenging culture, where

00:16:49.730 --> 00:16:51.050 align:middle line:90%
she didn't have much.

00:16:51.050 --> 00:16:53.660 align:middle line:84%
And she didn't get
to go to school.

00:16:53.660 --> 00:16:55.430 align:middle line:90%
She couldn't write and read.

00:16:55.430 --> 00:16:58.310 align:middle line:84%
So an American woman
came to her village

00:16:58.310 --> 00:16:59.990 align:middle line:90%
and said, what are your dreams?

00:16:59.990 --> 00:17:03.500 align:middle line:84%
And she was like, how can I
possibly dream when for me it's

00:17:03.500 --> 00:17:04.849 align:middle line:90%
about survival?

00:17:04.849 --> 00:17:09.440 align:middle line:84%
And the American woman,
she kept asking her.

00:17:09.440 --> 00:17:12.170 align:middle line:84%
And then she said, well, if
I can do anything in my life,

00:17:12.170 --> 00:17:15.960 align:middle line:84%
I would love first to get
an education here and then

00:17:15.960 --> 00:17:16.760 align:middle line:90%
university.

00:17:16.760 --> 00:17:22.160 align:middle line:84%
And my biggest dreams would
be to have a PhD in America.

00:17:22.160 --> 00:17:24.920 align:middle line:84%
And she actually went
home to her mother,

00:17:24.920 --> 00:17:27.300 align:middle line:84%
and her mother said,
if you're going

00:17:27.300 --> 00:17:30.140 align:middle line:84%
to do all that, I think
you should add one more

00:17:30.140 --> 00:17:32.810 align:middle line:84%
dream for the betterment
of other people.

00:17:32.810 --> 00:17:34.910 align:middle line:90%
So she did add--

00:17:34.910 --> 00:17:38.480 align:middle line:84%
her last dream was to come back
to the community, if she could

00:17:38.480 --> 00:17:41.060 align:middle line:84%
achieve all that, come
back to the community

00:17:41.060 --> 00:17:44.690 align:middle line:84%
and then help other girls
not going through what

00:17:44.690 --> 00:17:46.040 align:middle line:90%
she had to go through.

00:17:46.040 --> 00:17:51.110 align:middle line:84%
So to make a very long story
short, she achieved all that--

00:17:51.110 --> 00:17:52.250 align:middle line:90%
unbelievable.

00:17:52.250 --> 00:17:56.090 align:middle line:90%
And she got her PhD.

00:17:56.090 --> 00:17:57.530 align:middle line:90%
Oprah heard about her.

00:17:57.530 --> 00:17:59.390 align:middle line:90%
She got invited for the show.

00:17:59.390 --> 00:18:03.470 align:middle line:84%
She got invited to the show, and
she got invited a second time.

00:18:03.470 --> 00:18:08.120 align:middle line:84%
And Oprah gave her $1.5
million to go back and achieve

00:18:08.120 --> 00:18:10.710 align:middle line:84%
her last dream, which
is unbelievable.

00:18:10.710 --> 00:18:13.160 align:middle line:90%
And now she has 12 schools.

00:18:13.160 --> 00:18:17.930 align:middle line:84%
And what I love about that
story is that she had nothing,

00:18:17.930 --> 00:18:22.010 align:middle line:84%
and she had all the
hurdles and challenges

00:18:22.010 --> 00:18:24.780 align:middle line:84%
that I think we all
feel that we have.

00:18:24.780 --> 00:18:28.490 align:middle line:84%
But at least most
of us have a phone.

00:18:28.490 --> 00:18:33.500 align:middle line:84%
Most of us have food, internet,
and somewhere to stay,

00:18:33.500 --> 00:18:36.170 align:middle line:90%
and she didn't have all that.

00:18:36.170 --> 00:18:39.080 align:middle line:84%
And that's why I like
sharing her story,

00:18:39.080 --> 00:18:42.080 align:middle line:84%
because I think it's
so powerful for people

00:18:42.080 --> 00:18:44.840 align:middle line:84%
to hear that she
achieved all that.

00:18:44.840 --> 00:18:46.880 align:middle line:84%
And what she's doing now
is just unbelievable.

00:18:46.880 --> 00:18:51.140 align:middle line:84%
