to start the morning on my own.

00:20:53.950 --> 00:20:56.470 align:middle line:84%
So I have something that
I call my holy hour.

00:20:56.470 --> 00:21:00.580 align:middle line:84%
And my ideal morning would
start at 5:00 AM, when

00:21:00.580 --> 00:21:05.200 align:middle line:84%
it's still dark or the sun is
coming up and it's just me.

00:21:05.200 --> 00:21:10.270 align:middle line:84%
And I always start with writing
three pages, morning pages,

00:21:10.270 --> 00:21:12.130 align:middle line:90%
inspired by Julia Cameron.

00:21:12.130 --> 00:21:15.760 align:middle line:84%
And then I always have loads
of ideas out of writing

00:21:15.760 --> 00:21:16.820 align:middle line:90%
whatever comes to mind.

00:21:16.820 --> 00:21:18.362 align:middle line:84%
And then I have
another journal where

00:21:18.362 --> 00:21:19.450 align:middle line:90%
I capture all those ideas.

00:21:19.450 --> 00:21:21.700 align:middle line:84%
Because the first morning
pages I don't actually save,

00:21:21.700 --> 00:21:23.140 align:middle line:90%
but the other one I do.

00:21:23.140 --> 00:21:25.210 align:middle line:84%
And then I always
do some learning,

00:21:25.210 --> 00:21:27.790 align:middle line:84%
because that is something
that really inspires me.

00:21:27.790 --> 00:21:31.640 align:middle line:84%
And that keeps me going,
and I always want to share.

00:21:31.640 --> 00:21:35.118 align:middle line:84%
And that's one of my
values is to learn,

00:21:35.118 --> 00:21:37.160 align:middle line:84%
but then also to share
everything that I learned.

00:21:37.160 --> 00:21:39.760 align:middle line:84%
So I do that in the morning,
and then I meditate.

00:21:39.760 --> 00:21:41.890 align:middle line:84%
And then between 6:00
and 7:00-- this is ideal.

00:21:41.890 --> 00:21:46.280 align:middle line:84%
I'm not perfect in any
way, so this is my ideal.

00:21:46.280 --> 00:21:48.160 align:middle line:84%
And then I exercise
between 6:00 and 7:00.

00:21:48.160 --> 00:21:50.620 align:middle line:84%
That could be running,
walking, yoga,

00:21:50.620 --> 00:21:53.560 align:middle line:84%
whatever I feel like doing,
just some kind of movement.

00:21:53.560 --> 00:21:55.600 align:middle line:84%
And then by the time
I'm home at 7:00

00:21:55.600 --> 00:21:57.760 align:middle line:84%
and then it's all about
getting the kids to school

00:21:57.760 --> 00:22:01.750 align:middle line:84%
or whatever I need
to do, that is really

00:22:01.750 --> 00:22:05.230 align:middle line:84%
what gets me to feel that
I really care for myself.

00:22:05.230 --> 00:22:07.570 align:middle line:84%
Because whatever that
day then brings me--

00:22:07.570 --> 00:22:10.400 align:middle line:84%
it could be important
meetings or urgent meetings,

00:22:10.400 --> 00:22:13.660 align:middle line:84%
or it could be other
people's agenda,

00:22:13.660 --> 00:22:15.715 align:middle line:84%
I feel like I had
that self-care.

00:22:15.715 --> 00:22:17.590 align:middle line:84%
But I think everyone
needs to find their own,

00:22:17.590 --> 00:22:19.010 align:middle line:90%
whatever that is for them.

00:22:19.010 --> 00:22:21.940 align:middle line:84%
It could be that you go spend
a lot of time in nature.

00:22:21.940 --> 00:22:25.060 align:middle line:84%
Or one of, I think, the
most important things

00:22:25.060 --> 00:22:27.670 align:middle line:84%
in today's world is
disconnect to reconnect in

00:22:27.670 --> 00:22:31.180 align:middle line:84%
terms of turning those phones
off sometimes, or the screens.

00:22:31.180 --> 00:22:34.372 align:middle line:84%
Because I think we
are on all the time.

00:22:34.372 --> 00:22:35.830 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes it's
really difficult

00:22:35.830 --> 00:22:38.130 align:middle line:84%
