00:27:47.630 --> 00:27:50.020 align:middle line:84%
to this interview what
some of these values

00:27:50.020 --> 00:27:52.910 align:middle line:84%
might be so they can start
to identify with them

00:27:52.910 --> 00:27:53.710 align:middle line:90%
a little bit?

00:27:53.710 --> 00:27:55.918 align:middle line:84%
So if they're struggling,
what's this idea of values,

00:27:55.918 --> 00:27:58.107 align:middle line:84%
you can share what some
of the words would be

00:27:58.107 --> 00:27:59.440 align:middle line:90%
or what some of your values are.

00:27:59.440 --> 00:28:01.420 align:middle line:84%
>> My biggest value
is actually learning,

00:28:01.420 --> 00:28:03.190 align:middle line:90%
like personal development.

00:28:03.190 --> 00:28:06.340 align:middle line:84%
And it took me a long time to
realize that that was actually

00:28:06.340 --> 00:28:07.930 align:middle line:90%
one of my biggest learning.

00:28:07.930 --> 00:28:10.210 align:middle line:84%
Because I love learning
in so many different ways,

00:28:10.210 --> 00:28:13.810 align:middle line:84%
but I don't really love
learning about new cars.

00:28:13.810 --> 00:28:15.910 align:middle line:84%
It was really about
improving my life.

00:28:15.910 --> 00:28:19.180 align:middle line:84%
And that's what our
purpose of kikki.K

00:28:19.180 --> 00:28:22.630 align:middle line:84%
is, to inspire people to live
their best life every day.

00:28:22.630 --> 00:28:25.750 align:middle line:84%
So finding values that
are true to yourself,

00:28:25.750 --> 00:28:27.580 align:middle line:84%
you really need
to spend some time

00:28:27.580 --> 00:28:31.212 align:middle line:84%
to think about if you
could do anything today,

00:28:31.212 --> 00:28:32.920 align:middle line:84%
what would you actually
spend time doing?

00:28:32.920 --> 00:28:36.920 align:middle line:84%
And then really think about,
what would I choose to do?

00:28:36.920 --> 00:28:39.100 align:middle line:84%
And I think that's
why Dr. Demartini does

00:28:39.100 --> 00:28:43.210 align:middle line:84%
such a great job, because he
doesn't cover just one thing.

00:28:43.210 --> 00:28:45.550 align:middle line:84%
Because I think he gives
a really good example

00:28:45.550 --> 00:28:49.650 align:middle line:84%
that most people who you ask
about their values, if I say

00:28:49.650 --> 00:28:51.470 align:middle line:84%
is financial freedom
one of your values,

00:28:51.470 --> 00:28:52.960 align:middle line:90%
most people would say yes.

00:28:52.960 --> 00:28:55.783 align:middle line:84%
And then you ask, what
are you doing about it?

00:28:55.783 --> 00:28:57.700 align:middle line:84%
And most people will
say, well, I'm not really

00:28:57.700 --> 00:29:01.430 align:middle line:84%
doing anything because it's
not their highest value.

00:29:01.430 --> 00:29:04.000 align:middle line:84%
So, for example, for
me, financial freedom

00:29:04.000 --> 00:29:07.210 align:middle line:84%
is not my highest value,
but freedom on my own time

00:29:07.210 --> 00:29:09.380 align:middle line:90%
is really, really high up there.

00:29:09.380 --> 00:29:11.230 align:middle line:84%
So I think you should
spend some time

00:29:11.230 --> 00:29:13.640 align:middle line:84%
and really work out what
is important to you.

00:29:13.640 --> 00:29:18.280 align:middle line:84%
And if you can have a
whole free day, what would

00:29:18.280 --> 00:29:19.690 align:middle line:90%
you spend your time doing?

00:29:19.690 --> 00:29:23.590 align:middle line:84%
And that often gets you a bit
of an idea on what actually

00:29:23.590 --> 00:29:26.860 align:middle line:84%
is true, not just what
you say is true, but also

00:29:26.860 --> 00:29:29.910 align:middle line:84%
what you actually want
to spend your time doing.

00:29:29.910 --> 00:29:30.710 align:middle line:90%
>> Well done.

00:29:30.710 --> 00:29:31.130 align:middle line:90%
I love it.

00:29:31.130 --> 00:29:33.050 align:middle line:84%
Freedom is one of my
top ones, I discovered.

00:29:33.050 --> 00:29:36.080 align:middle line:84%
And it was very low down
previously in my old values

00:29:36.080 --> 00:29:37.725 align:middle line:90%
that I discovered.

00:29:37.725 --> 00:29:39.350 align:middle line:84%
And then when I sort
of realigned them,

00:29:39.350 --> 00:29:40.520 align:middle line:90%
I'm like, no, freedom.

00:29:40.520 --> 00:29:45.140 align:middle line:84%
And also-- I'm trying to
word this the right way,

00:29:45.140 --> 00:29:49.070 align:middle line:84%
but inspiring others, helping
unlock potential in people,

00:29:49.070 --> 00:29:54.860 align:middle line:84%
helping unlock possibility
to heal, to connect, to move

00:29:54.860 --> 00:29:56.600 align:middle line:90%
through challenges in life.

00:29:56.600 --> 00:29:59.570 align:middle line:84%
And that became what
we did after that.

00:29:59.570 --> 00:30:02.270 align:middle line:84%
Food Matters was not yet born
when I did that values work.

00:30:02.270 --> 00:30:03.905 align:middle line:84%
And then from the
freedom component,

00:30:03.905 --> 00:30:05.900 align:middle line:84%
getting to make films
and travel the world

00:30:05.900 --> 00:30:08.570 align:middle line:84%
and meet interesting people
is ultimate alignment.

00:30:08.570 --> 00:30:12.360 align:middle line:84%
So really my work became
my values in a lot of ways.

00:30:12.360 --> 00:30:13.200 align:middle line:90%
It's powerful stuff.

00:30:13.200 --> 00:30:14.480 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah, absolutely.

00:30:14.480 --> 00:30:17.240 align:middle line:84%
And I really do think that
life is too short not to do

00:30:17.240 --> 00:30:20.130 align:middle line:90%
what you love, and every day.

00:30:20.130 --> 00:30:22.190 align:middle line:84%
When I did a podcast
yesterday, even that

00:30:22.190 --> 00:30:24.900 align:middle line:90%
was out of my comfort zone.

00:30:24.900 --> 00:30:26.430 align:middle line:90%
I just love it.

00:30:26.430 --> 00:30:29.030 align:middle line:84%
And talking about things like
this, this is what I love.

00:30:29.030 --> 00:30:32.830 align:middle line:84%
And sharing and
learning is definitely

00:30:32.830 --> 00:30:35.510 align:middle line:90%
high up there on my values.

00:30:35.510 --> 00:30:38.810 align:middle line:84%
>> Being of service to others
I think is something that gets

00:30:38.810 --> 00:30:42.890 align:middle line:84%
grossly under looked when
we start to do goal setting.

00:30:42.890 --> 00:30:46.740 align:middle line:84%
But in a lot of the work that
I've done interviewing people,

00:30:46.740 --> 00:30:50.060 align:middle line:84%
it's in serving others that
so much fulfillment, so much

00:30:50.060 --> 00:30:51.530 align:middle line:90%
happiness comes from that.

00:30:51.530 --> 00:30:54.020 align:middle line:84%
You've got the stationary
company, and it's beautiful,

00:30:54.020 --> 00:30:56.443 align:middle line:84%
and you make people's
homes look amazing.

00:30:56.443 --> 00:30:57.860 align:middle line:84%
But I don't think
anything lit you

00:30:57.860 --> 00:31:00.560 align:middle line:84%
up as much as giving
those kids that stationery

00:31:00.560 --> 00:31:01.850 align:middle line:90%
in those schools.

00:31:01.850 --> 00:31:05.060 align:middle line:84%
So can you speak to
how much you think

00:31:05.060 --> 00:31:08.360 align:middle line:84%
giving back and having a
greater purpose to your work

00:31:08.360 --> 00:31:09.988 align:middle line:90%
and serving others is important?

00:31:09.988 --> 00:31:12.530 align:middle line:84%
Is that something that you think
people should be focusing on

00:31:12.530 --> 00:31:13.790 align:middle line:90%
more and more?

00:31:13.790 --> 00:31:17.520 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I think everyone
should focus on what they love.

00:31:17.520 --> 00:31:19.550 align:middle line:84%
And I think if you
do what you love,

00:31:19.550 --> 00:31:22.640 align:middle line:84%
and because of
doing all that you

00:31:22.640 --> 00:31:26.720 align:middle line:84%
are able to share your
passions and your purpose

00:31:26.720 --> 00:31:29.698 align:middle line:84%
with other people, and that
means that they are inspired,

00:31:29.698 --> 00:31:30.990 align:middle line:90%
and then they will be inspired.

00:31:30.990 --> 00:31:32.720 align:middle line:90%
So it's a lovely ripple effect.

00:31:32.720 --> 00:31:37.070 align:middle line:90%
But one of my values is sharing.

00:31:37.070 --> 00:31:40.610 align:middle line:84%
Since the day I can
remember, I always love,

00:31:40.610 --> 00:31:42.620 align:middle line:84%
if I'm reading a great
book, I always share it,

00:31:42.620 --> 00:31:44.255 align:middle line:84%
and I absolutely
love sharing it.

00:31:44.255 --> 00:31:46.910 align:middle line:84%
So that became part of
the kikki.K purpose.

00:31:46.910 --> 00:31:49.640 align:middle line:84%
And I always encourage
people to share

00:31:49.640 --> 00:31:52.430 align:middle line:90%
whatever field they are in.

00:31:52.430 --> 00:31:55.520 align:middle line:84%
Because there is always
someone behind you

00:31:55.520 --> 00:31:58.850 align:middle line:84%
in terms of starting out in life
that could do with some help.

00:31:58.850 --> 00:32:02.450 align:middle line:84%
And there is always someone
who is less fortunate than you.

00:32:02.450 --> 00:32:05.277 align:middle line:84%
So whatever you can do
to help, and I always say

00:32:05.277 --> 00:32:06.860 align:middle line:84%
it doesn't have to
be a lot of things.

00:32:06.860 --> 00:32:09.770 align:middle line:84%
It could be that you read
to a child that might not

00:32:09.770 --> 00:32:12.110 align:middle line:84%
have parents, or it could
be that you, instead

00:32:12.110 --> 00:32:15.350 align:middle line:84%
of buying two coffees,
you take that money

00:32:15.350 --> 00:32:17.790 align:middle line:84%
and you put that into
something that you care about.

00:32:17.790 --> 00:32:19.910 align:middle line:84%
So I think you can
do so many things,

00:32:19.910 --> 00:32:21.540 align:middle line:84%
but you need to be
passionate about it.

00:32:21.540 --> 00:32:23.720 align:middle line:84%
So if you are passionate
about something

00:32:23.720 --> 00:32:27.110 align:middle line:84%
that you have been affected
by, I think support that.

00:32:27.110 --> 00:32:29.160 align:middle line:84%
Because there's so much
to do in the world.

00:32:29.160 --> 00:32:31.700 align:middle line:84%
And I think sometimes we
get a little bit overwhelmed

00:32:31.700 --> 00:32:33.608 align:middle line:90%
by wanting to save the world.

00:32:33.608 --> 00:32:35.900 align:middle line:84%
And when you look at the
world like, where do you start

00:32:35.900 --> 00:32:39.200 align:middle line:90%
and what can I do?

00:32:39.200 --> 00:32:41.170 align:middle line:84%
What can me as an
individual do to this world,

00:32:41.170 --> 00:32:45.380 align:middle line:84%
that it feels completely
unrealistic and really

00:32:45.380 --> 00:32:46.370 align:middle line:90%
hard to get to.

00:32:46.370 --> 00:32:48.620 align:middle line:84%
But you can start
small, and you can

00:32:48.620 --> 00:32:51.110 align:middle line:84%
start where you are and do
something that you love.

00:32:51.110 --> 00:32:53.900 align:middle line:84%
And because of that,
then inspire others.

00:32:53.900 --> 00:32:57.980 align:middle line:84%
And then that becomes
hopefully a better world.

00:32:57.980 --> 00:32:58.790 align:middle line:90%
>> Well said.

00:32:58.790 --> 00:32:59.870 align:middle line:90%
I concur.

00:32:59.870 --> 00:33:02.180 align:middle line:84%
You're a force for good,
Kristina, really good.

00:33:02.180 --> 00:33:04.340 align:middle line:84%
I think we've covered some
incredible topics today.

00:33:04.340 --> 00:33:06.588 align:middle line:84%
I feel very grateful
for our conversation.

00:33:06.588 --> 00:33:08.630 align:middle line:84%
My last question would
be, is there anything else

00:33:08.630 --> 00:33:09.860 align:middle line:90%
you think you wanted to add?

00:33:09.860 --> 00:33:11.850 align:middle line:84%
Any quote that you
miss saying, anything

00:33:11.850 --> 00:33:14.450 align:middle line:84%
you think from the book that
you think is worth mentioning,

00:33:14.450 --> 00:33:19.780 align:middle line:84%
or if there's any last sort of
idea or quote or any finale.

00:33:19.780 --> 00:33:20.580 align:middle line:90%
>> Yep.

00:33:20.580 --> 00:33:25.230 align:middle line:84%
So I think I want to go back a
little bit on the discomfort.

00:33:25.230 --> 00:33:31.010 align:middle line:84%
So I think having big dreams
is sometimes daunting,

00:33:31.010 --> 00:33:35.420 align:middle line:84%
and it's out of your comfort
zone if you dream really big.

00:33:35.420 --> 00:33:38.360 align:middle line:84%
And if you start dreaming
and you have all these dreams

00:33:38.360 --> 00:33:41.090 align:middle line:84%
and goals and you put that
into that bucket thinking,

00:33:41.090 --> 00:33:44.960 align:middle line:84%
that is so daunting and
it's so uncomfortable

00:33:44.960 --> 00:33:48.320 align:middle line:84%
even to think about how I'm
going achieve those dreams.

00:33:48.320 --> 00:33:51.740 align:middle line:84%
And then you go in
your normal life,

00:33:51.740 --> 00:33:53.960 align:middle line:84%
and you just keep
going where you are.

00:33:53.960 --> 00:33:57.230 align:middle line:84%
And you actually think
about that my life could

00:33:57.230 --> 00:34:00.215 align:middle line:90%
be much more whatever that is.

00:34:00.215 --> 00:34:02.090 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't mean you have
to start big things,

00:34:02.090 --> 00:34:04.040 align:middle line:90%
but do what you love.

00:34:04.040 --> 00:34:08.360 align:middle line:84%
And knowing that you potentially
could do more with your life,

00:34:08.360 --> 00:34:09.590 align:middle line:90%
that's also discomfort.

00:34:09.590 --> 00:34:11.960 align:middle line:84%
And I always think,
which discomfort zone

00:34:11.960 --> 00:34:13.255 align:middle line:90%
do you want to be in?

00:34:13.255 --> 00:34:14.630 align:middle line:84%
And I always choose
the one where

00:34:14.630 --> 00:34:18.389 align:middle line:84%
I want to make sure that I
do as much as I possibly can.

00:34:18.389 --> 00:34:20.953 align:middle line:84%
Because I think that at
the end of your life,

00:34:20.953 --> 00:34:23.120 align:middle line:84%
you want to make sure that
you did whatever you can.

00:34:23.120 --> 00:34:24.995 align:middle line:84%
Because we don't know
how many lives we have.

00:34:24.995 --> 00:34:28.699 align:middle line:84%
But assuming this is the
one and only life we have,

00:34:28.699 --> 00:34:31.350 align:middle line:84%
I think you want to
make the most of it.

00:34:31.350 --> 00:34:34.730 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes big dreams
could be doing less.

00:34:34.730 --> 00:34:39.120 align:middle line:84%
So it doesn't have to be
big, crazy goals, starting

00:34:39.120 --> 00:34:40.400 align:middle line:90%
a global business or whatever.

00:34:40.400 --> 00:34:42.025 align:middle line:84%
It could be that you
actually just want

00:34:42.025 --> 00:34:45.570 align:middle line:84%
to have a Sunday off
and go out in nature.

00:34:45.570 --> 00:34:48.860 align:middle line:84%
So I think it will be
discomfort whatever you choose,

00:34:48.860 --> 00:34:51.310 align:middle line:90%
so why not go for your dreams?

00:34:51.310 --> 00:34:52.110 align:middle line:90%
>> Beautiful.

00:34:52.110 --> 00:34:53.602 align:middle line:90%
Thank you so much for your time.

00:34:53.602 --> 00:34:54.810 align:middle line:90%
It's awesome to speak to you.

00:34:54.810 --> 00:34:57.260 align:middle line:84%
And I love the
continual evolution

00:34:57.260 --> 00:35:00.530 align:middle line:84%
of the kikki.K brand
and your new focus

00:35:00.530 --> 00:35:03.740 align:middle line:84%
on goal setting and
inspiring people to dream

00:35:03.740 --> 00:35:04.980 align:middle line:90%
and also giving back.

00:35:04.980 --> 00:35:06.090 align:middle line:84%
So thank you for what
you do in the world.

00:35:06.090 --> 00:35:06.990 align:middle line:90%
I appreciate it.

00:35:06.990 --> 00:35:09.110 align:middle line:84%
>> Thank you for having me,
and thank you for all that

00:35:09.110 --> 00:35:09.910 align:middle line:90%
you're doing.

